gomodel:SYNGO_5381  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099067 replaced by GO:0098954" , "Rationale: Figure 5, 7: Biochemical fractions prepared from rat brain homogenate showed that Vti1a and Vti1b are both present in synaptosomal fractions. Where Vti1a was also present in synaptic vesicle fractions (and confirmed with electron microscopy), Vti1b was barely detectable in SVs. This suggests some Vti1b could be localized to synaptic vesicles, but the majority of synaptic Vti1b is not. This was later confirmed by mass-spectrometry, where Vti1b was detected in P2 but only sparingly in SV fractions (PMID:33376223).\n\nFigure 8: immunoisolations from rat brain homogenate showed that Vti1b could be immunoisolated with synaptobrevin, rab3a, and rab5 beads but to a smaller extend than Vti1a.\n\nIt is known that Vti1b is a late endosome SNARE protein;\n- Recombinant endobrevin (Vamp8), syntaxin 7, syntaxin 8 and vti1b (each lacking their transmembrane domain) form protein complexes (PMID:11101518).\n- Crystal structure of an endosomal SNARE core complex containing four SNAREs: syntaxin 7, syntaxin 8, vti1b and endobrevin/VAMP-8 (PMID:11786915).\n\nTaken together, Vti1b localization to presynaptic endosomal structures is inferred. Based on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: Results, Figure 8 legend: \"Vti1a-β was found on immunoisolated synaptic vesicles and endosomes. A 50,000 × g supernatant of rat brain homogenate was incubated with antibodies against synaptobrevin\"\n\nantibody:\n\"Antibodies. Antisera were raised in rabbits against a fusion protein containing GST and the amino acids 1-207 of mouse Vti1b (pBK9)\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5381" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

